 <!--912-->Endurance of Dwarves x4<br>
 <!--45-->Gimli&#39;s Battle Axe x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Kind of a self-explanatory deck, you want to bid low, like 1 or 2. Since playing your sites is helpful but not required it doesn&#39;t really matter if you go first or not. You want to use your trackers and get the Under the Watching Eyes out early. The Desperate Defense of the Ring will cripple your opponent if he plays with few companions and you get all 4 out. Orc Banners make sure that you can deal out some extra wounds in the archery phase. Try to save the Hates and use them all at once to kill a companion if possible. <br>
<br>
For the Free Peoples, try to get the weapons out ASAP, use Gandalf&#39;s Cart to cycle your hand. Gimli can become a real powerhouse with 4 Endurance of Dwarves on him, Gandalf and Aragorn help to make sure that your Fellowship doesn&#39;t get creamed at the later sites. Overall, it&#39;s the Shadow side that wins the game for you. Have Fun! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
